products.title: MT RAINIER TOUR FROM SEATTLE
products.short_description: Experience a Mt. Rainier day tour during summer or winter.
products.description: Visit Mt. Rainier from Seattle with our professional, enthusiastic, and informative guides. Travel in our clean, comfortable 24-passenger mini-coaches with large windows, high-back seats, and air-conditioning. The time of year will determine the route and accessibility of tours. In peak months, experience old-growth forests, wildflower-filled meadows, and thundering waterfalls on this tour of glacier-clad Mt. Rainier. Hike and walk a little, or not at all: there are options for all abilities. Enjoy lunch at a Mt. Rainier cafe (when open) or buy a picnic lunch along the way when we stop at a grocery store. Visit the interpretive center at Paradise or Sunrise to learn even more about the mountain’s glaciers, plants, and animals on this exciting day trip to Mt. Rainier from Seattle.

features.value: Admission/Park fees included.
Lunch is not provided.
Pickup available from SeaTac!
No minimum required number of guests – we run all scheduled tours!

faqs.question: What is your cancellation policy?
faqs.answer: We offer full refunds on all tours canceled at least 24 hours in advance of the tour’s start time. There are no refunds in the 24 hours leading up to the tour.

faqs.question: Do I need to bring food?
faqs.answer: Food options in the park are extremely limited, but we stop at a grocery store on our way out there.

faqs.question: What should I wear to Mount Rainier National Park?
faqs.answer: Please dress for comfort and the weather. Comfortable shoes (ideally hiking boots with good traction and water resistance) will make a huge difference in your enjoyment of the tour.

products.description: The adventure begins from your hotel, where your personal local expert will pick your party up in a Pearl Chevrolet Suburban LTZ. Work with your Mt. Rainier guide to create the best itinerary and stops for your group. See and experience places within the National Park that our public tour cannot reach. Expect professional, courteous service and an entertaining Mt. Rainier day tour. We operate clean, well-maintained vehicles, featuring leather interior and comfortable seating. Our Suburban seats 5 comfortably (6 max) with 1 front passenger seat, 2 captain’s chairs in the middle row, and bench seating for 3 (2 comfortably) in the rear.
